sentences: She became a professor at the Budapest Franz Liszt Academy where she remained until 1942.
She then concertized widely throughout Europe in the 1950s and made recordings with the Westminster Label.

sentences: Edith Farnadi (25 September 1921 – 12 or 14 December 1973) was a Hungarian pianist.
She received her diploma from the Musical Academy in Budapest when she was 17 years old.
At the International Musical afternoons at the Budapest Palais, she performed many times with Bronisław Huberman.
